New Records: Tyler O’Neill hit his second walk-off homer of the season and fifth overall
Key Match Events: The game went into extra innings with Tyler O’Neill hitting a three-run homer in the 10th inning to secure the victory
The Orioles tied the game in the eighth inning with a home run by Anthony Santander but the Red Sox won in the 10th
Post-Match Reflections: This was the final regular-season meeting between the Red Sox and Orioles
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was the last regular-season matchup between the two teams
Jackson Holliday had a fielding error which led to Romy Gonzalez reaching base
Others: Brennan Bernardino was placed on the injured list, and Cam Booser was reinstated
